{{See also|List of colors (compact)|List of color palettes|Index of color-related articles}}

[[File:Colouring pencils.jpg|right|thumb|Color is an important part of the [[visual art]]s, [[fashion]], [[interior design]] and many other fields and disciplines.]]

The following is a comprehensive '''list of colors''' that are included in the Wikipedia articles about [[color]]. A large portion of the color swatches below are taken from [[Domain-specific language|domain-specific]] naming schemes such as [[X11 color names|X11]] or [[HTML#HTML version timeline|HTML4]]. [[RGB color model|RGB]] values are given for each swatch because such standards are defined in terms of the [[sRGB|sRGB color space]]. It is not possible to accurately convert many of these swatches to [[CMYK]] values because of the differing [[gamut]]s of the two spaces, but the [[color management]] systems built into [[operating system]]s and [[Graphics software|image editing software]] attempt such conversions as accurately as possible.

The [[HSV color space|HSV]] (hue, saturation, value) color space values, also known as HSB (hue, saturation, brightness), and the [[hex triplet]]s (for [[HTML color names|HTML web colors]]) are also given in the following table. Colors that appear on the [[Web colors|web-safe color]] palette{{mdash}}which includes the sixteen [[Indexed color|named colors]]{{mdash}}are noted.<ref name="W3C">{{cite web|url=http://www.w3.org/MarkUp/Guide/Style|title=Dave Raggett's Introduction to CSS|publisher=[[World Wide Web Consortium]]|date=8 April 2002|first=Dave|last=Raggett|authorlink=Dave Raggett|accessdate=9 December 2010}}</ref> (Those four named colors corresponding to the neutral grays can be rendered with any ''hue'' value, which is effectively ignored{{mdash}}i.e., left blank.)<!--WEB SAFE COLORS: There are 216 such colors, with each triad = (00, 33, 66, 99, CC, or FF). All exact colors in this list are marked. Many others are proximal (within say 15 units per triad), but are not yet marked. -->

The appearance of the actual color swatches displayed below will look different on your computer  depending on many parameters, such as the properties of your display device, your [[color management]] settings and the viewing surround conditions, most notably the [[color spectrum]] of the [[Lighting|illumination]] source.<ref>[http://www.ipa.org/bulletin/articles/view_cond.php3 Viewing surround conditions, IPA.org]</ref> Also, [[color name|Color naming]] is ambiguous and arbitrary, and varies among people and cultures, with no single swatch adequately representing any particular color name. Computer displays have a somewhat limited gamut, so many colorful [[pigment]]s cannot be represented on a screen at all and [[computer simulation]] of the [[natural world]] is, at best, a rough approximation.

