== Colors by shade ==
=== White ===
{{Main|White|Variations of white}}
White is a balanced combination of all the colors of the [[visible light spectrum]], or of a pair of [[complementary color]]s, or of three or more colors, such as [[additive primary]] colors. It is a neutral or achromatic (''without color'') color, like [[black]] and [[gray]].
{{Shades of white|nocategory=yes|state=plain}}

=== Pink ===
{{Main|Pink}}
Pink is a [[tint]] of red, created by adding some white.
{{Shades of pink|nocategory=yes|state=plain}}

=== Red ===
{{Main|Red|Variations of red}}
Red is any of a number of similar colors evoked by [[light]], consisting predominantly of the longest wavelengths discernible by the human eye, in the [[wavelength]] range of roughly 625â750 [[Nanometre|nm]]. It is considered one of the [[additive color|additive]] [[primary color]]s.
{{Shades of red|nocategory=yes|state=plain}}

=== Orange ===
{{Main|Orange (colour)}}
Orange is the color in the visible spectrum between red and yellow with a wavelength around 585&nbsp;â 620&nbsp;nm. In the [[HSV color space]], it has a hue of around 30Â°.

{{Shades of orange|nocategory=yes|state=plain}}

=== Brown ===
{{Main|Brown}}
Brown colors are dark or muted shades of reds, oranges, and yellows on the RGB and CMYK color schemes. In practice, browns are created by mixing two complementary colors from the RYB color scheme (combining all three primary colors). In theory, such combinations should produce black, but produce brown because most commercially-available blue pigments tend to be comparatively weaker; the stronger red and yellow colors prevail, thus creating the following tones.
{{Shades of brown|nocategory=yes|state=plain}}

=== Yellow ===
{{Main|Yellow}}
Yellow is the color of light with wavelengths predominately in the range of roughly 570â580&nbsp;nm. In the HSV color space, it has a hue of around 60Â°. It is considered one of the [[subtractive color|subtractive]] [[primary color]]s.
{{Shades of yellow|nocategory=yes|state=plain}}

=== Gray ===
{{Main|Gray}}
Achromatic grays are colors between black and white with no hue. Chromatic grays are achromatic grays mixed with warm hues such as orange (''warm grays'') or cool hues such as azure (''cool grays''). This gray color template includes both achromatic and chromatic grays.
{{Shades of gray|nocategory=yes|US=yes|state=plain}}

=== Green ===
{{Main|Green|Variations of green}}
Green is a color, the perception of which is evoked by light having a spectrum dominated by energy with a [[wavelength]] of roughly 520â570&nbsp;[[Nanometre|nm]]. It is considered one of the additive [[primary color]]s.
{{Shades of green|nocategory=yes|state=plain}}

=== Cyan ===
{{Main|Cyan}}
Cyan is any of the colors in the blue-green range of the [[visible spectrum]], i.e., between approximately 520 and 420&nbsp;nm. It is considered one of the [[subtractive color|subtractive]] [[primary color]]s.
{{Shades of cyan|nocategory=yes|state=plain}}

=== Blue ===
{{Main|Blue|Variations of blue}}
Blue is a color, the perception of which is evoked by light having a spectrum dominated by energy with a [[wavelength]] of roughly 440â490&nbsp;nm. It is considered one of the additive [[primary color]]s.
{{Shades of blue|nocategory=yes|state=plain}}

=== Violet ===
{{Main|Violet (color)|Purple}}
Violet is any of the colors the perception of which is evoked by light having a spectrum dominated by energy with a wavelength of roughly 380â450&nbsp;nm. Tones of violet tending towards the blue are called indigo. Purple colors are colors that are various blends of violet light or blue light and red light.
{{Shades of violet|nocategory=yes|state=plain}}

==Web colors==
{{Main|Web colors}}
These are the colors used by computer graphic designers for web page designing. These colors are displayed on the monitors of computers.
{{Web Colors|state=plain}}

== Fictional colors ==

*'''[[List of Nebulous episodes#First_series|Garrow]]'''&nbsp; and '''Infra-White'''&nbsp; â colors invented in the ''[[Nebulous]]'' episode "Madness is a Strange Colour". The first color both colors affect the human mind in odd ways, either destroying or creating sanity. Professor Nebulous claims that he discovered Infra-White by looking ''underneath and behind'' the visible spectrum.
*'''[[Fuligin]]'''&nbsp;â both a color and a textile having that color, associated with the Guild of Torturers in [[Gene Wolfe]]'s book, ''[[The Shadow of the Torturer]]''. The color is defined as "the color that is darker than black" and also as "the color of soot."
*'''[[Grue and bleen]]'''&nbsp;â colors that change after an arbitrary, but fixed time; coined by [[Charles Dodgson]]{{Citation needed|date=June 2008}} and used by philosopher Nelson Goodman to illustrate what he calls "the new [[riddle of induction]]."
*'''[[Races and species in The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy#Hooloovoo|Hooloovoo]]'''&nbsp;â a superintelligent shade of the color blue in ''[[The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy]]'' series by [[Douglas Adams]].
*'''[[Discworld (world)#Octarine|Octarine]]'''&nbsp;â the color of magic in the [[Discworld]] fantasy novels, described as resembling a fluorescent greenish-yellow purple.
*'''[[Squant]]'''&nbsp;â a fourth primary color publicized by the experimental band [[Negativland]] in 1993.
*[[A Voyage to Arcturus#Names|'''Jale''' and '''Ulfire''']]&nbsp;â new primary colors (shades of ultraviolet?) in ''[[A Voyage to Arcturus]]'' by [[David Lindsay (novelist)|David Lindsay]].
*'''[[The Colour Out of Space]]'''&nbsp;â a vaguely-described alien hue, from the story of that name by [[H. P. Lovecraft]].
*The colors [[The Stars My Destination|'''tang''' and '''burn''']] are colors in the [[infrared]] range seen by the [[albino]] [[mutant]] Olivia Presteign (whose [[Visual perception|vision]] only functions in the infrared) in the 1956 [[science fiction]] novel ''[[The Stars My Destination]]'' by [[Alfred Bester]].<ref>[[Anthony Boucher|Boucher, Anthony]], Editor ''A Treasury of Great Science Fiction'' Garden City, New York:1959âDoubleday Volume Twoâ''The Stars My Destination'' by Alfred Bester, Pages 361â522âColor reference Page 465</ref>
*'''Htun''' is a color similar to black only seen by gnomes in the book ''[[Fairest]]'' by [[Gail Carson Levine]].
*'''Sangoire''' is a color of red 'so dark and saturated it [is] almost black', seen in the '''[[Kushiel's Legacy]] Series''' by [[Jacqueline Carey]].
*'''Blellow''' is the name given to the color created by Reese of ''[[Malcolm in the Middle]]'' when he mixed blue and yellow together. Otherwise known as green.
*'''Celestewhite''' is a color invented by Carlos Argentino for his lengthy topographical poem intended to describe the entire world, in '''[[Jorge Luis Borges]]' '''[[The Aleph (short story)|The Aleph]].  It "actually suggests the sky, an element of utmost importance in the landscape of the Down Under."

